This can be done with [local scopes](https://laravel.com/docs/5.7/eloquent#local-scopes). If you are also familiar with [recursion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recursion_(computer_science)) the code I&#39;m going to write will be easy to understand. Anwyay everything is explained with the comments. 

```php
/**
 * Retrieve recursively the related children building a tree.
 * Pay attention! this scope may cause A LOT of performance problems. Expecially when there are a lot of children / nephews
 * 
 * @param  Buider  $query
 * @param  integer  $deep  
 * @param  integer $index
 * @return Builder
 */
public function scopeTree($query, $deep, $index = 0) {
  // Increment index
  $index++;

  // Current model is root, let&#39;s find the id for base case.
  $id = $this-&gt;getKey();

  // Now build the recursive nested query
  return $query-&gt;whereHas(&#39;children&#39;, function($query) use ($deep, $index, $id) {
    // If deep is lower than index, it means we have to add a node to the tree
    if($deep &lt; $index) {
      // Recursion
      $query-&gt;tree($deep, $index);
    } else {
      // Base case
      $query-&gt;where(&#39;parent_id&#39;, &#39;=&#39;, $id);
    }
  });
}
```

Anyway this function may cause A LOT of performance problems, so it should be better not to go &quot;too deep&quot; if there are a lot of records inside the database.

